    <custom_item>
      system      : "Linux"
      type        : FILE_CONTENT_CHECK_NOT
      description : "VCEM-67-000025 - ESX Agent Manager must not enable support for TRACE requests."
      info        : "'Trace' is a technique for a user to request internal information about Tomcat. This is useful during product development but should not be enabled in production. Allowing an attacker to conduct a Trace operation against ESX Agent Manager will expose information that would be useful to perform a more targeted attack. ESX Agent Manager provides the 'allowTrace' parameter to disable responding to Trace requests."
      solution    : "Navigate to and open:

/usr/lib/vmware-eam/web/conf/server.xml

Navigate to and locate:

'allowTrace='true''

Remove the 'allowTrace='true'' setting."
